                "invention-title": [
                    "Preparation method of shale layered polymer, flaky extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent, preparation method of flaky extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent and application of flaky extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent in hydrogen isotope separation",
                    "一种页岩层状聚合物的制备方法、片状极微孔炭质吸附剂及其制备方法和氢同位素分离应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a preparation method of a shale layered polymer, a sheet-shaped extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent, a preparation method of the sheet-shaped extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent and application of the sheet-shaped extremely-microporous carbon adsorbent to hydrogen isotope separation. The preparation method of the shale layered polymer comprises the steps that hydroquinone, p-phenylenediamine and terephthalaldehyde are sequentially added into N, N-dimethylformamide according to the molar ratio of (0-1): 1: 2 to be dissolved, and the molar ratio of p-phenylenediamine to N, N-dimethylformamide ranges from 1: 20 to 1: 200; and polymerizing the solution, and carrying out vacuum drying to obtain the scribable polymer. The sheet-shaped ultra-microporous carbon adsorbent is integral microporous carbon obtained by carbonizing a shale layered polymer precursor, and has slit-type ultra-micropores of which the pore diameters are intensively distributed at 0.40-0.47 nm. In a 77K hydrogen and deuterium gas static adsorption test, the sheet-shaped carbon adsorbent with an optimized pore structure can realize that the deuterium gas adsorption amount is higher than that of hydrogen. In a dynamic low-temperature penetration experiment, the separation of hydrogen and deuterium gas is successfully realized; in addition, the flaky ultra-microporous carbon adsorbent can also realize the adsorption separation of ethane and ethylene."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开一种页岩层状聚合物的制备方法、片状极微孔炭质吸附剂及其制备方法和氢同位素分离应用。页岩层状聚合物的制备方法包括将对苯二酚、对苯二胺和对苯二甲醛按照(0～1):1:2的摩尔比依次加入N,N‑二甲基甲酰胺中溶解，对苯二胺与N,N‑二甲基甲酰胺的摩尔比为1:20～1:200；将上述溶液进行聚合，经真空干燥得到可涂写的聚合物。片状极微孔炭质吸附剂是通过将页岩层状聚合物前驱体经过碳化得到的整体式微孔炭，具有孔径集中分布在0.40‑0.47nm的狭缝型极微孔。在77K氢气和氘气静态吸附测试中，孔结构优化的片状炭质吸附剂可以实现氘气吸附量高于氢气。在动态低温穿透实验中，也成功的实现氢气和氘气的分离；此外，该片状极微孔炭质吸附剂还可以实现乙烷乙烯的吸附分离。"
                }
            ]
